---
// Section 5 — Risk Reversal
// "Why commission is the point." — structural rationale for the pricing model,
// followed by the "Three zeros" data module. Borrows SaaS pricing-table visual
// language (ruled columns, big numerics, eyebrow labels) on the deep-forest
// accent ground (not flat black — warmer, on-brand). No product UI.
//
// Body is a two-column editorial grid on desktop (one paragraph per column)
// so the argument fills the measure rather than leaving a cold right column.
//
// Research delta #2 integrated as a quiet category-creator line under the
// closer: echoes the hero's "risk-free infrastructure" language and names who
// it's built for. Deliberately low-volume — not a slogan, a clarification.
---

<section
  id="commission"
  class="py-32 md:py-44 px-6 md:px-10 lg:px-16"
  style="background: var(--color-bg);"
>
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <!-- Heading -->
    <h2
      data-reveal
      class="font-serif leading-[1.02] tracking-tight max-w-3xl"
      style="
        color: var(--color-ink);
        font-size: clamp(2rem, 5.2vw, 4.25rem);
      "
    >
      Why commission is the point.
    </h2>

    <!-- Body: two paragraphs, two-column editorial layout on desktop -->
    <div
      data-reveal
      data-reveal-delay="1"
      class="mt-10 md:mt-14 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 md:gap-12 lg:gap-16 text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed"
      style="color: var(--color-ink-muted);"
    >
      <p>
        Most agencies charge retainers because forecasting hours across clients
        gives them predictable cashflow. The trade-off is that they get paid the
        same whether your campaign converts or doesn't. That's a bad bet for you.
      </p>
      <p>
        Commission-only inverts it. We make money when you make money. We don't
        take campaigns we can't close. We don't stretch a campaign across more
        hours than it needs. The incentive is aligned by construction.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Dark data module: Three zeros -->
    <div
      data-reveal
      data-reveal-delay="2"
      class="mt-20 md:mt-28 rounded-md overflow-hidden"
      style="background: var(--color-accent); color: var(--color-dark-text);"
    >
      <div class="px-8 md:px-12 lg:px-16 py-14 md:py-20">
        <!-- Eyebrow -->
        <div
          class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em]"
          style="color: rgba(250, 250, 250, 0.55);"
        >
          Three zeros that matter
        </div>

        <!-- Three zeros grid — stacks on mobile, three columns on md+ -->
        <div
          class="mt-10 md:mt-16 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-y-10"
        >
          <!-- Zero 1 — Retainer -->
          <div class="md:pr-8 md:border-r" style="border-color: rgba(250, 250, 250, 0.15);">
            <div
              class="font-serif leading-[0.9] tracking-tight"
              style="font-size: clamp(4.5rem, 9vw, 8rem);"
            >
              $0
            </div>
            <div
              class="mt-5 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em]"
              style="color: rgba(250, 250, 250, 0.7);"
            >
              Retainer
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Zero 2 — Platform fee -->
          <div class="md:px-8 md:border-r" style="border-color: rgba(250, 250, 250, 0.15);">
            <div
              class="font-serif leading-[0.9] tracking-tight"
              style="font-size: clamp(4.5rem, 9vw, 8rem);"
            >
              $0
            </div>
            <div
              class="mt-5 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em]"
              style="color: rgba(250, 250, 250, 0.7);"
            >
              Platform fee
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Zero 3 — Minimum spend -->
          <div class="md:pl-8">
            <div
              class="font-serif leading-[0.9] tracking-tight"
              style="font-size: clamp(4.5rem, 9vw, 8rem);"
            >
              $0
            </div>
            <div
              class="mt-5 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em]"
              style="color: rgba(250, 250, 250, 0.7);"
            >
              Minimum spend
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Closer — hairline rule + warm line + quiet category framing -->
        <div
          class="mt-14 md:mt-20 pt-10 md:pt-14 border-t"
          style="border-color: rgba(250, 250, 250, 0.15);"
        >
          <p
            class="font-serif leading-snug max-w-2xl"
            style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.6vw, 2.25rem);"
          >
            A commission on deals we close, together.
          </p>
          <p
            class="mt-5 text-sm md:text-base max-w-xl leading-relaxed"
            style="color: rgba(250, 250, 250, 0.6);"
          >
            The risk-free infrastructure, built for the companies databases
            failed and agencies priced out.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
